The paper deals with reducing the complexity of applying linear operators in high dimension by approximately factorizing the corresponding matrix into few sparse factors. This is a problem that is relevant to several areas of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), numerical analysis (cs.NA), computer vision (cs.CV), information theory (cs.IT), and data structures (cs.DS). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper. Among these, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category as the paper deals with matrix factorization, which is a common technique in machine learning.
